docs = [
{"id":"doc_001","topic":"Artificial Intelligence","text":"Artificial Intelligence (AI) refers to the simulation of human intelligence in machines that are programmed to think, learn, and make decisions. AI systems can perform tasks such as reasoning, problem-solving, understanding natural language, and perception. AI is broadly classified into narrow AI and general AI. Applications include healthcare, finance, and autonomous vehicles."},

{"id":"doc_002","topic":"Machine Learning","text":"Machine Learning is a subset of AI that allows systems to learn patterns from data without explicit programming. Types include supervised, unsupervised, and reinforcement learning. It is used in spam detection, recommendation systems, and fraud detection."},

{"id":"doc_003","topic":"Supervised Learning","text":"Supervised learning uses labeled data to train models. It maps input to output and is used in classification and regression tasks like spam detection and price prediction."},

{"id":"doc_004","topic":"Unsupervised Learning","text":"Unsupervised learning works on unlabeled data and finds hidden patterns. It is used in clustering and dimensionality reduction."},

{"id":"doc_005","topic":"Reinforcement Learning","text":"Reinforcement learning involves an agent learning through rewards and penalties. It is used in robotics and gaming."},

{"id":"doc_006","topic":"K Means Clustering","text":"K-means is an unsupervised algorithm that groups data into clusters using centroids. It is widely used in segmentation."},

{"id":"doc_007","topic":"Support Vector Machine","text":"SVM is a supervised algorithm that finds the optimal hyperplane for classification. It works well in high-dimensional data."},

{"id":"doc_008","topic":"Neural Networks","text":"Neural networks are models inspired by the human brain consisting of layers of neurons. Used in deep learning applications."},

{"id":"doc_009","topic":"Overfitting","text":"Overfitting happens when a model learns noise and performs poorly on new data. It can be reduced using regularization."},

{"id":"doc_010","topic":"Underfitting","text":"Underfitting occurs when a model is too simple to capture patterns, leading to poor performance."}
]